Well, something one has to consider...  the forces of Norrath *have* been leaning towards Good as of late...  perhaps Evil shall once again prevail.  Were it against a different city, I perhaps would have joined your ranks to bring my weight onto the Scales.<br>
<br>
However: know that to perpetuate this Evil that will one day become more powerful than good, I will wield it as ably as any Teir'Dal or Ogre.  If you so much as break a single hair on the head of any of my friends who will be there to guard Ak'Anon, you will someday find your heart on the ground, still palpitating, awash in the power of the Storms.  You'll wish that Dark Elves had better dark vision than they do even now, for someday I will appear from those shadows.  Perhaps not the day of the thirtieth, perhaps not the thirtieth of August or September, but I will bide my time.  But know that halflings have very long memories, and this is something that I will remember.<br>
